OL,3,CCaller told 999 operator he'd murder
OL,4,Cher amid rise in abuse for emergency
OL,5,Cstaff
OL,7,F"One caller said he was going to stab
OL,8,Fme in the neck as I left work.
OL,10,F"We understand that these are patients
OL,11,Fhaving the worst day of their life,
OL,12,Fbut that doesn't mean we should bear
OL,13,Fthe brunt of their frustration when
OL,14,Fwe're only trying to help.
OL,16,F"It's hard to then put that aside and
OL,17,Fbe calm and compassionate for the next
OL,18,Fcaller, so you're constantly on edge."
