OL,3,CCaller told 999 operator he'd murder
OL,4,Cher amid rise in abuse for emergency
OL,5,Cstaff
OL,7,F"They play an important role in
OL,8,Fgathering vital information to arrange
OL,9,Fthe best help quickly, but shouting,
OL,10,Fswearing and threats will only delay
OL,11,Fthat help.
OL,13,F"That's not to mention the devastating
OL,14,Fand long-term emotional impact it can
OL,15,Fhave on call takers, some of whom have
OL,16,Fno choice but to leave the role.
OL,18,F"We understand that when people call
OL,19,Fus, they might be frightened, in shock
OL,20,Fand upset, but that's not an excuse to
OL,21,Fabuse our staff.
